  "analyst_notes": "NHPC is India's largest hydroelectric power company and a pure-play renewable energy utility with 100% clean capacity (hydro 94%, solar 6%, wind <1%). Key strengths: (1) Zero coal exposure - no stranded asset risk; (2) Negligible emissions (0.0018 tCO2/MWh); (3) Massive expansion pipeline (46 GW total including 19 GW pumped storage); (4) AAA domestic credit rating with government backing. Key concerns: (1) No company-specific net-zero target (only aligned with India 2070); (2) No SBTi commitment; (3) Elevated Debt/EBITDA ~6x from capital-intensive hydro projects; (4) All 5 B5 credit metrics weak - only Debt/Capital passes. FY25 cash flow impacted by Teesta floods (-30.7% YoY). ETCB outcomes: B1 PASS (0% coal), B2 PASS (minimal emissions), B3 PASS (no thermal), B4 PASS (100% RE share), B5 FAIL (1/5 metrics). Final score: 4/5 Medium-high tier."
